        </ul>

        <h4>In-depth Explanation of DHA Certification and Compliance</h4>
        <p>
          DHA certification ensures healthcare providers meet strict international standards.
          Professionals undergo licensing exams, continuous training, and regular audits. Providers
          must maintain patient records, uphold sterility, and follow approved protocols for
          transparency and accountability.
        </p>
        <p>
          Choosing DHA-certified providers minimizes risks, guarantees safe formulations, and
          ensures professional oversight. Patients also benefit from transparent pricing and
          established channels for support or redress.
        </p>

        <h4>Step-by-Step Procedure of IV Drip Therapy at Home</h4>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <b>Initial Consultation &amp; Screening</b> – Remote or in-person review of medical
            history, allergies, and wellness goals.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Scheduling &amp; Preparation</b> – Choose a convenient time; minimal preparation
            required.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Nurse Arrival &amp; Vitals Check</b> – DHA-certified nurse arrives, checks blood
            pressure, temperature, and pulse.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>IV Drip Administration</b> – Sterile catheter insertion with fluids infused at a
            controlled rate.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Monitoring During Session</b> – 30–60 minutes of close supervision for comfort and
            safety.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Completion &amp; Dressing</b> – Catheter removed, sterile dressing applied, waste
            disposed per DHA protocols.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Aftercare &amp; Follow-Up</b> – Hydration advice, symptom monitoring, and provider
            check‑ins.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h4>Physical Sensations, Duration, and Outcomes</h4>
        <p>
          Most patients feel only mild discomfort at insertion, similar to a blood test. Some notice
          a cool sensation as fluids flow. Sessions last 30–60 minutes. Benefits may include
          improved hydration, energy, mental clarity, or symptom relief within hours, with
          additional improvements in 24–48 hours.
        </p>

        <h4>Benefits and Potential Risks</h4>
        <p>
          <b>Benefits:</b> rapid absorption, hydration, energy boost, stronger immunity, tailored
          wellness support.
        </p>
        <p>
          <b>Risks:</b> minor bruising, redness, or irritation at insertion site; rare dizziness or
          allergic reactions. DHA screening and certified care minimize these risks.
        </p>

